<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-20T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-20T17:00:00-05:00" n="1168" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1168">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/276</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Parker</persName>, representing American
                                interests</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-20T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 20, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>430. Your telegram 382, September seventh, 5 p.m. Following telegram
                            received from Salina Cruz: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Properties were again raided September 11th by rebels and
                                    ex-Constitutionalist soldiers. All the provisions and much
                                    personal property stolen, native administrator and laborers have
                                    been forced leave. This will entail loss of crops which should
                                    now be harvested. Loss will be over ten thousand American
                                    dollars which the owners are not in position to lose.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Urge upon appropriate authorities necessity for prompt and effective
                            action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>